reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These napkins are excellent in every aspect. First, the napkins themselves are very nice and thick, definitely not your average grocery store variety. They also have a classy look to them, making them perfect for birthday parties, romantic candlelight dinners, or formal occasions. They are also a great value considering that you get 200 pieces for only ten dollars, which is the same price point as normal napkins. Honestly, I may just start buying these from now on as my regular napkins. They are very durable, too, so if you spill a bit of liquid, one napkin can be used instead of three or four because you can flip it over and also use the inside of it. It may actually be more efficient to use these instead. I highly recommend these, 5/5!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Elegant cocktail napkins
reviews.reviewText: This is a very nice pack of cocktail napkins. I like them in black, which I think has an elegant look, and the scalloped edges are very unique and attractive. I love how they look when fanned out on the table or in a napkin holder. I should add that these napkins are not flimsy, but rather are on the thicker side. I think that makes them even more useful, since they are almost coaster -like ( without being too stiff). I highly recommend these for any occasion!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These napkins have a time and place. These are not the kind of napkins you will use when eating wings. The napkins are really not for wiping your hands, as they are rather stiff. You will use this napkin when serving drinks or small desserts, such as cookies. The napkin is absorbent enough to protect surfaces from condensation or small drink spills. The napkins themselves are very pretty and can be used for many occasions. The scalloped edge adds a touch of fanciness, and there is a little design imprinted on the edges.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute cocktail napkins!
reviews.reviewText: These scalloped cocktail napkins would be cute for a baby shower, wedding, or even a sage green shade to complement the green colors of St. Patrick's Day party. Folded in fourths and 200 in a package - ready to go. The inside is white, so the green color isn't on both sides. But most people would unfold it once maybe and I doubt anyone would unfold it all the way to see the reverse side. Pretty sage green and I love the scalloped edge!
